@startuml notification-pipeline
' ============================================================
' AlharisTech Platform — Notification Delivery Pipeline
' Domain Event → Preferences → Template → Routing → Delivery → Retry → DLQ
' ============================================================

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 10

skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor #D4E6F1
  BorderColor #2980B9
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor #FDEBD0
  BorderColor #E67E22
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #D5F5E3
  BorderColor #27AE60
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FEF9E7
  BorderColor #F1C40F
  FontSize 9
}

skinparam arrow {
  FontSize 9
}

skinparam box {
  BackgroundColor #F4F6F7
  BorderColor #AAB7B8
  FontSize 10
  FontStyle bold
}

title **AlharisTech Platform — Notification Delivery Pipeline**
title **خط أنابيب توصيل الإشعارات — من الحدث إلى التسليم**

box "Domain Services (Publishers)" #E8F0FE
  participant "Service\nDomain" as ServiceDomain
  participant "Support\nDomain" as SupportDomain
  participant "Commerce\nDomain" as CommerceDomain
  participant "Identity\nDomain" as IdentityDomain
endbox

box "Notification Service" #D5F5E3
  participant "Event Bus\nSubscriber" as EventBus
  participant "Notification\nDispatcher" as Dispatcher
  participant "Preference\nEngine" as PrefEngine
  participant "Template\nEngine" as TemplateEngine
  participant "Channel\nRouter" as ChannelRouter
endbox

box "Delivery Channels" #FDEBD0
  participant "Email\nProvider\n(Resend/SES)" as EmailProvider
  participant "SMS\nProvider\n(Twilio/Unifonic)" as SMSProvider
  participant "Push\nProvider\n(Firebase/OneSignal)" as PushProvider
endbox

box "Reliability & Monitoring" #FDEDEC
  participant "Delivery Log\nPostgreSQL" as DeliveryLog
  participant "Retry Queue\nBullMQ" as RetryQueue
  participant "Dead Letter\nQueue" as DLQ
endbox

actor "Admin\nمدير" as Admin
database "PostgreSQL\npreferences / templates" as DB

== EVENT INGESTION — استقبال الأحداث ==

note over ServiceDomain, IdentityDomain
  **Domain Events Published:**
  · OrderStatusChanged (Service)
  · TicketOpened, TicketResolved (Support)
  · PaymentCompleted, ShipmentCreated (Commerce)
  · UserRegistered, AccountLocked (Identity)
  · ... 40+ event types across domains
endnote

ServiceDomain -> EventBus : Publish **OrderStatusChanged**\n{ orderId, oldStatus: "in_progress",\n  newStatus: "completed",\n  customerId: "uuid-123",\n  changedBy: "uuid-456",\n  timestamp }

SupportDomain -> EventBus : Publish **TicketAssigned**\n{ ticketId, ticketNumber: "TKT-2026-000143",\n  assignedTo: "uuid-789",\n  customerId: "uuid-456" }

CommerceDomain -> EventBus : Publish **PaymentCompleted**\n{ orderId, orderNumber: "ORD-2026-000042",\n  amount: 253.00, currency: "SAR",\n  customerId: "uuid-456" }

EventBus -> Dispatcher : Route events to notification handlers
note right of EventBus
  **Event Routing Map:**
  OrderStatusChanged → notifyCustomer, notifyEmployee
  TicketAssigned → notifyEmployee, notifyCustomer
  PaymentCompleted → notifyCustomer
  UserRegistered → notifyCustomer (welcome)
  AccountLocked → notifyCustomer (security alert)
endnote

== PREFERENCE CHECK — التحقق من التفضيلات ==

Dispatcher -> PrefEngine : checkUserPreferences(customerId, eventType)

PrefEngine -> DB : SELECT * FROM notification_preferences\nWHERE user_id = ?

DB --> PrefEngine : { preferences }

note right of PrefEngine
  **User Notification Preferences:**
  {rn    global_enabled: true,
    channels: {
      email: {
        enabled: true,
        types: ["order", "ticket", "payment"]
      },
      sms: {
        enabled: true,
        types: ["payment", "security"],
        quiet_hours: { start: "22:00", end: "08:00" }
      },
      push: {
        enabled: true,
        types: ["order", "ticket", "payment", "security"]
      }
    },
    locale: "ar"
  }
endnote

alt Notifications globally disabled
  PrefEngine --> Dispatcher : SKIP — notifications disabled
  note right of Dispatcher : Record in delivery_log as "skipped: preference"
else Globally enabled
  PrefEngine -> PrefEngine : Check if event type allowed\nfor each channel

  PrefEngine --> Dispatcher : { channels: { email: true, sms: true, push: true },\n  locale: "ar" }
end

== TEMPLATE SELECTION & RENDERING — اختيار القالب وتعبئته ==

Dispatcher -> TemplateEngine : selectTemplate(eventType, locale, channel)

TemplateEngine -> DB : SELECT * FROM notification_templates\nWHERE event_type = 'OrderStatusChanged'\nAND locale = 'ar'\nAND channel IN ('email', 'sms', 'push')

DB --> TemplateEngine : { templates: [email_template, sms_template, push_template] }

note right of TemplateEngine
  **Template Structure (Handlebars):**
  email_order_status_changed_ar:
    subject: "{{siteName}} - تحديث حالة الطلب #{{referenceNumber}}"
    body_html: "<p>عزيزي {{customerName}}،</p>
      <p>تم تغيير حالة طلبك #{{referenceNumber}}
      من <strong>{{oldStatusAr}}</strong>
      إلى <strong>{{newStatusAr}}</strong>.</p>"
    body_text: "..."
    sms_body: "{{siteName}}: طلبك #{{referenceNumber}}
      تغير إلى {{newStatusAr}}"
    push_title: "تحديث الطلب"
    push_body: "طلبك #{{referenceNumber}}: {{newStatusAr}}"
endnote

TemplateEngine -> TemplateEngine : **Render with variables:**
note right of TemplateEngine
  **Variable Substitution:**
  {rn    orderId → lookup order details
    customerId → lookup customer name (ar/en)
    referenceNumber → from order payload
    oldStatus → oldStatus mapped to Arabic label
    newStatus → newStatus mapped to Arabic label
    siteName → "منصة الحارس تك"
    dashboardLink → https://alharistech.com/ar/orders/{id}
  }
endnote

TemplateEngine -> DB : Lookup additional context:\n· Customer: first_name_ar, last_name_ar\n· Order: reference_number, service name_ar\n· Status labels (ar): in_progress → "قيد المعالجة"\n  completed → "مكتمل"

DB --> TemplateEngine : Context data

TemplateEngine -> TemplateEngine : Render Handlebars templates\nwith full context → final messages

TemplateEngine --> Dispatcher : {rn  email: { subject, html, text },
  sms: { body },
  push: { title, body }
}

== MULTI-CHANNEL ROUTING — توجيه متعدد القنوات ==

Dispatcher -> ChannelRouter : dispatch(channel, renderedMessage, user)

par Parallel delivery to all enabled channels
  ChannelRouter -> ChannelRouter : Route to EMAIL
  note right of ChannelRouter
    **Channel: Email**
    Provider: Resend (primary) / AWS SES (fallback)
    Format: HTML + plain text
    Max size: 100KB
  endnote

  ChannelRouter -> EmailProvider : POST /emails\n{ from: "AlharisTech <noreply@alharistech.com>",\n  to: "customer@example.com",\n  subject: "{{rendered_subject}}",\n  html: "{{rendered_html}}",\n  text: "{{rendered_text}}",\n  headers: { "X-Entity-Ref-ID": "uuid" } }

  EmailProvider -> EmailProvider : Queue → SMTP → Inbox
  EmailProvider --> ChannelRouter : { messageId, status: "queued" }

  ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : Log email attempt\n{ channel: "email", messageId, status: "queued" }
end

par
  ChannelRouter -> ChannelRouter : Route to SMS

  alt Within quiet hours (22:00-08:00)
    ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : Log SMS deferred\n(reason: quiet_hours)
    note right of ChannelRouter
      **Quiet Hours:**
      SMS delivery delayed until 08:00.
      Stored in scheduled queue.
      Priority: security alerts bypass quiet hours.
    endnote
  else Outside quiet hours or security event
    ChannelRouter -> SMSProvider : POST /messages\n{ to: "+9665XXXXXXXX",\n  body: "{{rendered_sms_body}}" }

    SMSProvider -> SMSProvider : Route to carrier → Deliver
    SMSProvider --> ChannelRouter : { sid, status: "sent" }

    ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : Log SMS attempt\n{ channel: "sms", sid, status: "sent" }
  end
end

par
  ChannelRouter -> ChannelRouter : Route to PUSH

  ChannelRouter -> PushProvider : POST /send\n{ tokens: ["device_token_xxx"],\n  notification: {\n    title: "{{push_title}}",\n    body: "{{push_body}}"\n  },\n  data: {\n    type: "order_status",\n    orderId: "uuid",\n    deepLink: "/ar/orders/uuid"\n  } }

  PushProvider -> PushProvider : FCM/APNs → Device
  PushProvider --> ChannelRouter : { success: 1, failure: 0 }

  ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : Log push attempt\n{ channel: "push", status: "delivered" }
end

== DELIVERY STATUS TRACKING — تتبع حالة التسليم ==

note over ChannelRouter, DeliveryLog
  **Delivery Status Workflow:**
  queued → sent → delivered / bounced / failed

  Webhooks from providers update
  delivery status asynchronously.
endnote

EmailProvider -> ChannelRouter : Webhook: email delivered\n{ messageId, event: "delivered" }
ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE delivery_log\nSET status = 'delivered', delivered_at = NOW()

EmailProvider -> ChannelRouter : Webhook: email bounced\n{ messageId, event: "bounced", reason }
ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE delivery_log\nSET status = 'bounced', error = reason

alt Email bounced (hard bounce)
  ChannelRouter -> DB : UPDATE notification_preferences\nSET email_enabled = false\n(auto-disable on hard bounce)
  note right of ChannelRouter
    Auto-suppress channel on hard bounce
    to protect sender reputation.
  endnote
end

== FAILURE & RETRY — الفشل وإعادة المحاولة ==

alt Delivery failed (provider error / timeout)
  ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE delivery_log\nSET status = 'failed', attempt_count = attempt_count + 1

  ChannelRouter -> RetryQueue : Enqueue retry job\n{ messageId, channel, attempt: 1, maxAttempts: 3 }

  note right of RetryQueue
    **Exponential Backoff Strategy:**
    |= Attempt |= Delay |
    | 1st | 1 minute |
    | 2nd | 5 minutes (5x) |
    | 3rd | 25 minutes (5x) |
    | Total | ~31 minutes before DLQ |
  endnote

  RetryQueue -> RetryQueue : Wait 1 minute (attempt 1)

  RetryQueue -> ChannelRouter : Retry delivery (attempt 1)

  alt Retry succeeds
    ChannelRouter -> EmailProvider : Re-send email
    EmailProvider --> ChannelRouter : OK
    ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE status = 'sent'\nattempt_count = 1
    ChannelRouter -> RetryQueue : REMOVE job (success)
  else Retry fails (attempt 1)
    ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE attempt_count = 2

    RetryQueue -> RetryQueue : Wait 5 minutes (attempt 2)
    RetryQueue -> ChannelRouter : Retry delivery (attempt 2)

    alt Retry succeeds
      ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE status = 'sent'
      ChannelRouter -> RetryQueue : REMOVE job
    else Retry fails (attempt 2)
      ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE attempt_count = 3

      RetryQueue -> RetryQueue : Wait 25 minutes (attempt 3)

      RetryQueue -> ChannelRouter : Final retry (attempt 3)

      alt Retry succeeds
        ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE status = 'sent'
        ChannelRouter -> RetryQueue : REMOVE job
      else All retries exhausted (attempt 3 failed)
        note right of DLQ
          **ALL RETRIES EXHAUSTED**
          Moving to Dead Letter Queue.
        endnote

        ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE status = 'permanent_failure'\nfailed_at = NOW()

        ChannelRouter -> DLQ : Enqueue dead letter\n{ messageId, channel, eventType,\n  user, attempts: 3, lastError,\n  originalPayload }

        DLQ -> Notify : Publish alert: **Admin Notification**
        Notify -> Admin : Email: "فشل توصيل إشعار - تحقق من DLQ"\n+ message details + error log
      end
    end
  end
end

== DEAD LETTER QUEUE MANAGEMENT — إدارة طابور الرسائل الميتة ==

note over DLQ, Admin
  **Dead Letter Queue (DLQ):**
  Stores messages that failed all retry attempts.
  Admin can:
  · View DLQ dashboard
  · Inspect failed message details
  · Manually retry (with reason)
  · Purge (after investigation)
  · Export for audit
endnote

Admin -> DLQ : GET /api/v1/admin/notifications/dead-letter\n?status=failed&channel=email&from=...

DLQ --> Admin : 200 { data: [...failedMessages],\n  meta: { total, page } }

Admin -> Admin : Inspect failed message:\n· Original event payload\n· Error details\n· Attempt history\n· User preferences at time of failure

alt Issue resolved (provider outage over / fixed)
  Admin -> DLQ : POST /api/v1/admin/notifications/dead-letter/{id}/retry

  DLQ -> ChannelRouter : Retry with original payload
  ChannelRouter -> EmailProvider : Re-send
  EmailProvider --> ChannelRouter : OK
  ChannelRouter -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE status = 'sent' (manual retry)
  ChannelRouter -> DLQ : REMOVE from DLQ
else Irrecoverable (invalid email / user deleted)
  Admin -> DLQ : POST /api/v1/admin/notifications/dead-letter/{id}/purge\n{ reason: "User account deleted" }

  DLQ -> DeliveryLog : UPDATE status = 'discarded'\nnote: "Purged by admin: {reason}"
end

== DELIVERY LOG & AUDIT — سجل التسليم والتدقيق ==

note over DeliveryLog, DB
  **= Delivery Log Schema =**

  |= Field |= Description |
  | id | UUID |
  | event_type | OrderStatusChanged, TicketOpened, ... |
  | user_id | Recipient user ID |
  | channel | email, sms, push |
  | message_id | Provider reference ID |
  | status | queued, sent, delivered, failed, bounced, permanent_failure, discarded |
  | attempt_count | 0–3 |
  | last_error | Provider error message |
  | retry_history | JSONB [{ attempt, timestamp, error }] |
  | template_id | Template used |
  | rendered_content | Rendered message (for debugging) |
  | created_at | Initial attempt timestamp |
  | delivered_at | Delivery confirmation timestamp |
  | failed_at | Final failure timestamp |
endnote

== BATCH & DIGEST — التجميع والملخص ==

note over Dispatcher, ChannelRouter
  **Notification Batching (Phase 2):**
  · Low-priority notifications batched hourly
  · Daily digest email for marketing/updates
  · Real-time for: payment, security, SLA alerts
  · User-configurable digest frequency
endnote

opt Batch notification (low priority)
  Dispatcher -> Dispatcher : Check batch eligibility:\n· Priority: low\n· Not a security event\n· User opted into digest

  Dispatcher -> DB : INSERT INTO notification_batch\n(user_id, event_type, payload, scheduled_for)

  note right of Dispatcher
    Cron job runs every hour.
    Aggregates pending notifications.
    Sends single digest message.
  endnote
end

== CHANNEL FAILOVER — تجاوز فشل القناة ==

note over ChannelRouter, PushProvider
  **Channel Failover Strategy:**
  · Primary Email: Resend → Fallback: AWS SES
  · Primary SMS: Twilio → Fallback: Unifonic (Saudi)
  · Primary Push: Firebase → Fallback: direct APNs/FCM
  · Provider selection based on availability + cost
endnote

ChannelRouter -> EmailProvider : Send via Resend (primary)

alt Resend unavailable (timeout / 5xx)
  ChannelRouter -> ChannelRouter : Switch to fallback provider

  ChannelRouter -> EmailProvider : Send via AWS SES (fallback)

  note right of ChannelRouter
    **Failover Logic:**
    · Circuit breaker: 5 failures → 60s cooldown
    · Health check: periodic ping to primary
    · Auto-recovery: switch back when healthy
  endnote

  EmailProvider --> ChannelRouter : OK (via fallback)
end

@enduml
